During an interview on ‘_Casual Conversations with The Wrestling Classic_,’ Bryan Danielson reveals that his contract expires slightly before All In 2024. Despite this, Danielson says he wants to wrestle at All In and WrestleDream in Washington before he goes part time.  
  
**_"The big one is Wembley. I want to make it to Wembley. My contract actually expires before Wembley. But I want to make it to Wembley. Because as a wrestling fan — one, last year’s All In was incredible. But then as a wrestling fan, that’s like a defining moment, when the British Bulldog beats Bret Hart. So you think of Wembley almost in these mythical terms.  
  
But I really want to be able to do Wembley and just see what that’s like, see what that feels like. So, yeah, that’s a big one for me.  
  
I’m not sure if I’ll make it, but one thing that would be a nice way to like kind of close everything out for me is to do my last match as a full-time wrestler at WrestleDream at the Tacoma Dome."_**

